1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,120
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:04,120 --> 00:00:05,120
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:05,120 --> 00:00:11,500
My name is Catherine and today we have part two of our series about small talk in English.
我是Catherine，今天我们带来关于英语闲聊系列的第二部分。

4
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:12,500
That's right.
没错。

5
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:16,460
So as we mentioned, small talk are very short, quick conversations about everyday things
正如我们提到的，闲聊是关于日常琐事的简短、快速的对话，

6
00:00:16,460 --> 00:00:21,340
like the weather and usually have this with a colleague very quickly or a friend maybe.
比如天气，通常和同事或朋友快速聊一聊。

7
00:00:21,340 --> 00:00:24,180
Yeah, maybe not someone you know very well too.
是啊，也可能是不太熟的人。

8
00:00:24,180 --> 00:00:25,180
Exactly.
正是。

9
00:00:25,180 --> 00:00:26,780
So we're going to take a look at part two.
那我们来看看第二部分。

10
00:00:26,780 --> 00:00:35,500
Why don't we listen to the dialogue and see what's going on.
我们不如听一下对话，看看发生了什么。

11
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:38,540
So Michelle, let me introduce you to Maria.
那么Michelle，让我把你介绍给Maria。

12
00:00:38,540 --> 00:00:39,900
She's my colleague from Brazil.
她是我来自巴西的同事。

13
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:41,380
Maria, this is Michelle.
Maria，这是Michelle。

14
00:00:41,380 --> 00:00:42,800
Hi Michelle.
嗨，Michelle。

15
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:44,820
So what do you do here in Shanghai?
那你在上海做什么？

16
00:00:44,820 --> 00:00:47,020
I mean, what work do you do?
我是说，你做什么工作？

17
00:00:47,020 --> 00:00:49,400
I work in advertising right now.
我现在做广告行业。

18
00:00:49,400 --> 00:00:50,460
How about you?
你呢？

19
00:00:50,460 --> 00:00:52,100
I'm actually in the wine business.
我实际上在葡萄酒行业。

20
00:00:52,100 --> 00:00:53,940
Oh, that sounds really great.
哦，听起来真不错。

21
00:00:53,940 --> 00:00:56,020
I love wine myself.
我自己也喜欢葡萄酒。

22
00:00:56,020 --> 00:00:58,340
Is this your first time to Shanghai, Maria?
这是你第一次来上海吗，Maria？

23
00:00:58,340 --> 00:01:00,580
No, actually I often visit.
不，实际上我经常来。

24
00:01:00,580 --> 00:01:04,220
I usually come to China for business at least once a year.
我通常每年至少来中国出差一次。

25
00:01:04,220 --> 00:01:06,240
Also I love the restaurants in Shanghai.
而且我喜欢上海的餐厅。

26
00:01:06,240 --> 00:01:08,420
So that's a good reason to come.
所以这也是来的好理由。

27
00:01:08,420 --> 00:01:09,420
Me too.
我也是。

28
00:01:09,420 --> 00:01:12,900
Actually, there's a great Brazilian restaurant I recommend.
实际上，我推荐一家很棒的巴西餐厅。

29
00:01:12,900 --> 00:01:17,340
I mean, the food is delicious, but the service isn't so good.
我是说，食物很美味，但服务不太好。

30
00:01:17,340 --> 00:01:21,060
I often like to get together with friends and have a great barbecue there.
我经常喜欢和朋友聚在一起，在那里吃烧烤。

31
00:01:21,060 --> 00:01:22,820
We should go there together sometime.
我们应该找个时间一起去那里。

32
00:01:22,820 --> 00:01:23,820
Wonderful idea.
好主意。

33
00:01:23,820 --> 00:01:24,820
I'd love that.
我很乐意。

34
00:01:24,820 --> 00:01:29,020
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

35
00:01:29,020 --> 00:01:33,140
So now let's take a look at some of these very interesting phrases we find in this dialogue
现在让我们看看对话中一些非常有趣的短语，

36
00:01:33,140 --> 00:01:37,160
in Language Takeaway.
在“语言要点”部分。

37
00:01:37,160 --> 00:01:39,620
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

38
00:01:39,620 --> 00:01:44,580
So the first phrase we have today is from the first sentence of this dialogue.
今天我们第一个短语来自对话的第一句话。

39
00:01:44,580 --> 00:01:49,300
James says, so Michelle, let me introduce you to Maria.
James说：“那么Michelle，让我把你介绍给Maria。”

40
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:50,300
That's right.
没错。

41
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:55,260
And the second phrase, introduce someone to or introduce you to.
第二个短语是“介绍某人给”或“把你介绍给”。

42
00:01:55,260 --> 00:01:58,980
Okay, let me introduce you to this person.
好的，让我把你介绍给这个人。

43
00:01:58,980 --> 00:02:01,380
So Marco, let me introduce you to my friend.
那么Marco，让我把你介绍给我的朋友。

44
00:02:01,380 --> 00:02:02,380
Right.
对。

45
00:02:02,380 --> 00:02:07,060
And this is something that you say when you want to tell the person, look, you're going
这是当你想要告诉对方“看，你要认识一个新朋友”时说的话。

46
00:02:07,060 --> 00:02:08,340
to meet someone new.
你要认识一个新朋友。

47
00:02:08,340 --> 00:02:11,220
Let me introduce you to my friend, Sally.
让我把你介绍给我的朋友Sally。

48
00:02:11,220 --> 00:02:15,780
And this is very important because it's polite and it's a way for you to say, okay, you two
这很重要，因为它很礼貌，也是一种方式让你说：“好了，你们俩不认识彼此。”

49
00:02:15,780 --> 00:02:17,340
don't know each other.
你们俩不认识彼此。

50
00:02:17,340 --> 00:02:21,100
Here, this is this person's name, this is this person's name.
这是这个人的名字，这是这个人的名字。

51
00:02:21,100 --> 00:02:25,100
It's very important when you are introducing people or when you're in a situation with
当你介绍别人时，或者当你和两个不认识彼此的人在一起时，这非常重要。

52
00:02:25,100 --> 00:02:27,180
two people who don't know each other.
两个不认识彼此的人。

53
00:02:27,180 --> 00:02:28,180
That's right.
没错。

54
00:02:28,180 --> 00:02:29,180
Exactly.
正是。

55
00:02:29,180 --> 00:02:31,260
So let me introduce you to someone.
所以让我把你介绍给某人。

56
00:02:31,260 --> 00:02:36,300
Now another key question here, I think probably one of the key questions when you meet someone
现在另一个关键问题，我认为可能是当你认识新朋友时的一个关键问题，你在聊天、闲聊、简短对话中，“你在这里做什么”或“你是做什么的？”

57
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:43,220
new, you're talking, small talk, short conversation, what do you do here or what do you do?
你是做什么的？

58
00:02:43,220 --> 00:02:44,220
What do you do?
你是做什么的？

59
00:02:44,220 --> 00:02:46,260
So this might sound like a very strange question.
这听起来可能是个很奇怪的问题。

60
00:02:46,260 --> 00:02:47,260
What do you do?
你是做什么的？

61
00:02:47,260 --> 00:02:48,260
Do you watch TV?
你看电视吗？

62
00:02:48,260 --> 00:02:49,740
Do you like to eat food?
你喜欢吃东西吗？

63
00:02:49,740 --> 00:02:52,700
No, but this means what job do you do?
不，但这意思是“你做什么工作？”

64
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:53,700
Right.
对。

65
00:02:53,700 --> 00:02:55,540
What type of work do you do?
你做什么类型的工作？

66
00:02:55,540 --> 00:02:56,540
Okay.
好的。

67
00:02:56,540 --> 00:02:57,540
So Marco, what do you do?
那么Marco，你是做什么的？

68
00:02:57,540 --> 00:02:59,340
I host an English podcast.
我主持一个英语播客。

69
00:02:59,340 --> 00:03:00,340
All right.
好的。

70
00:03:00,340 --> 00:03:01,340
Me too.
我也是。

71
00:03:01,340 --> 00:03:03,060
So this is the question.
所以这就是这个问题。

72
00:03:03,060 --> 00:03:07,420
Now don't get confused and remember that this is the typical way of asking someone what
现在别搞混了，记住这是问别人工作的典型方式。

73
00:03:07,420 --> 00:03:08,420
is their job.
问别人工作。

74
00:03:08,420 --> 00:03:14,260
If you say, what is your job or what is your occupation, what is your occupation?
如果你说“你的工作是什么”或“你的职业是什么”，“你的职业是什么？”

75
00:03:14,260 --> 00:03:16,180
It's too formal and it's kind of awkward.
那太正式了，而且有点尴尬。

76
00:03:16,180 --> 00:03:19,140
I don't think anyone has ever asked me what is your occupation.
我想没人问过我“你的职业是什么”。

77
00:03:19,140 --> 00:03:20,460
Now I rarely say that.
我很少这么说。

78
00:03:20,460 --> 00:03:23,420
I almost always say, what do you do?
我几乎总是说“你是做什么的？”

79
00:03:23,420 --> 00:03:26,220
Or maybe what type of work do you do?
或者“你做什么类型的工作？”

80
00:03:26,220 --> 00:03:28,460
Or what business are you in?
或者“你从事什么行业？”

81
00:03:28,460 --> 00:03:31,220
So this is our next phrase actually.
所以这其实是我们的下一个短语。

82
00:03:31,220 --> 00:03:32,220
Right.
没错。

83
00:03:32,220 --> 00:03:36,100
If someone asks you what business are you in or what industry are you in, you would
如果有人问你从事什么行业或属于哪个领域，你会

84
00:03:36,100 --> 00:03:40,060
say like in this case, Maria, she is in the wine business.
像这个例子中，玛丽亚，她从事葡萄酒行业。

85
00:03:40,060 --> 00:03:41,060
Okay.
好的。

86
00:03:41,060 --> 00:03:42,660
I'm in the wine business.
我从事葡萄酒行业。

87
00:03:42,660 --> 00:03:47,820
That means that my job has to do with selling or buying wine.
这意味着我的工作与买卖葡萄酒有关。

88
00:03:47,820 --> 00:03:52,540
So if we replace the noun wine with something else, for example, clothing.
所以如果我们把名词“葡萄酒”换成别的东西，比如“服装”。

89
00:03:52,540 --> 00:03:56,620
I'm in the clothing business or I'm in the cheese business.
我从事服装行业，或者我从事奶酪行业。

90
00:03:56,620 --> 00:03:57,620
Exactly.
完全正确。

91
00:03:57,620 --> 00:03:58,980
You can basically change it with anything.
你基本上可以换成任何东西。

92
00:03:58,980 --> 00:03:59,980
With any product.
任何产品。

93
00:03:59,980 --> 00:04:03,740
I guess if you sell computers, I'm in the computer business.
我想如果你卖电脑，就说我从事电脑行业。

94
00:04:03,740 --> 00:04:07,700
Or if you have anything to do with computers, you can say I'm in the computer business.
或者如果你和电脑有关，你可以说我从事电脑行业。

95
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:08,700
All right.
好的。

96
00:04:08,700 --> 00:04:09,700
So that's great.
那很棒。

97
00:04:09,700 --> 00:04:10,700
I'm in the hmm business.
我从事嗯……行业。

98
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:11,700
Exactly.
完全正确。

99
00:04:11,700 --> 00:04:12,700
All right.
好的。

100
00:04:12,700 --> 00:04:14,820
So now we know what the person does.
现在我们知道这个人做什么了。

101
00:04:14,820 --> 00:04:16,340
We continue asking questions.
我们继续问问题。

102
00:04:16,340 --> 00:04:17,340
You know, we're interested.
你知道，我们很感兴趣。

103
00:04:17,340 --> 00:04:20,500
We want to keep the conversation going a little while longer.
我们想让对话再持续一会儿。

104
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:22,300
We say, Oh wow, that's really great.
我们说，哦哇，那真的很棒。

105
00:04:22,300 --> 00:04:24,020
I love wine myself.
我自己也喜欢葡萄酒。

106
00:04:24,020 --> 00:04:26,620
Then we ask, is this your first time to Shanghai?
然后我们问，这是你第一次来上海吗？

107
00:04:26,620 --> 00:04:27,620
Okay.
好的。

108
00:04:27,620 --> 00:04:31,700
So is this your first time to Shanghai or in Shanghai?
所以是“这是你第一次来上海”还是“在上海”？

109
00:04:31,700 --> 00:04:35,540
This means is this your first time to visit Shanghai?
这意味着这是你第一次访问上海吗？

110
00:04:35,540 --> 00:04:36,540
That's right.
没错。

111
00:04:36,540 --> 00:04:42,500
The preposition here is always confusing for an ESL learner because sometimes do you say,
这里的介词对英语学习者来说总是很困惑，因为有时你会说，

112
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:44,300
is this your first time in Shanghai?
这是你第一次在上海吗？

113
00:04:44,300 --> 00:04:46,620
Is this your first time on Shanghai?
这是你第一次在上海上面吗？

114
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:47,860
Now we're saying to Shanghai.
现在我们说“来上海”。

115
00:04:47,860 --> 00:04:51,700
So in this case or in this type of question, both are correct.
所以在这种情况下或这类问题中，两种说法都正确。

116
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:54,140
Is this your first time in Shanghai?
这是你第一次在上海吗？

117
00:04:54,140 --> 00:04:55,780
Is this your first time to Shanghai?
这是你第一次来上海吗？

118
00:04:55,780 --> 00:04:56,780
All right.
好的。

119
00:04:56,780 --> 00:05:00,400
So I could also say, you know, if we're in Chicago, Hey Marco, is this your first time
所以我也可以说，你知道，如果我们在芝加哥，嘿马可，这是你第一次

120
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:01,620
in Chicago?
在芝加哥吗？

121
00:05:01,620 --> 00:05:05,260
But I have to ask if we are in that city.
但我必须问我们是否在那个城市。

122
00:05:05,260 --> 00:05:10,020
I can't say, okay, I'm in Chicago today, but Marco, is this your first time in New York?
我不能说，好吧，我今天在芝加哥，但马可，这是你第一次在纽约吗？

123
00:05:10,020 --> 00:05:12,700
Because we're not in New York right now.
因为我们现在不在纽约。

124
00:05:12,700 --> 00:05:13,700
That could be confusing.
那可能会让人困惑。

125
00:05:13,700 --> 00:05:19,100
So remember when you ask this question, you're asking about where you are today, right now.
所以记住，当你问这个问题时，你问的是你今天、现在所在的地方。

126
00:05:19,100 --> 00:05:20,100
Exactly.
完全正确。

127
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:21,100
Very good.
非常好。

128
00:05:21,100 --> 00:05:22,580
So on that note, let's take a break.
那么就此打住，我们休息一下。

129
00:05:22,580 --> 00:05:31,900
Let's listen to the dialogue again and we'll be back with some more phrases.
让我们再听一遍对话，然后我们会回来讲更多短语。

130
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:34,900
So Michelle, let me introduce you to Maria.
所以米歇尔，让我介绍你认识玛丽亚。

131
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:36,300
She's my colleague from Brazil.
她是我来自巴西的同事。

132
00:05:36,300 --> 00:05:37,780
Maria, this is Michelle.
玛丽亚，这是米歇尔。

133
00:05:37,780 --> 00:05:39,180
Hi, Michelle.
嗨，米歇尔。

134
00:05:39,180 --> 00:05:41,220
So what do you do here in Shanghai?
那么你在上海做什么？

135
00:05:41,220 --> 00:05:43,420
I mean, what work do you do?
我是说，你做什么工作？

136
00:05:43,420 --> 00:05:45,780
I work in advertising right now.
我现在做广告工作。

137
00:05:45,780 --> 00:05:46,840
How about you?
你呢？

138
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:48,500
I'm actually in the wine business.
我其实在葡萄酒行业。

139
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:50,340
Oh, that sounds really great.
哦，那听起来真的很棒。

140
00:05:50,340 --> 00:05:52,400
I love wine myself.
我自己也喜欢葡萄酒。

141
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:54,740
Is this your first time to Shanghai, Maria?
这是你第一次来上海吗，玛丽亚？

142
00:05:54,740 --> 00:05:56,940
No, actually, I often visit.
不，其实我经常来。

143
00:05:56,940 --> 00:06:00,580
I usually come to China for business at least once a year.
我通常每年至少来中国出差一次。

144
00:06:00,580 --> 00:06:02,620
Also I love the restaurants in Shanghai.
而且我喜欢上海的餐厅。

145
00:06:02,620 --> 00:06:04,820
So that's a good reason to come.
所以这是个来的好理由。

146
00:06:04,820 --> 00:06:05,820
Me too.
我也是。

147
00:06:05,820 --> 00:06:09,260
Actually, there's a great Brazilian restaurant I recommend.
其实，我推荐一家很棒的巴西餐厅。

148
00:06:09,260 --> 00:06:13,740
I mean, the food is delicious, but the service isn't so good.
我是说，食物很美味，但服务不太好。

149
00:06:13,740 --> 00:06:17,480
I often like to get together with friends and have a great barbecue there.
我经常喜欢和朋友聚在一起，在那里享受烧烤。

150
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:19,220
We should go there together sometime.
我们应该找个时间一起去那里。

151
00:06:19,220 --> 00:06:20,220
Wonderful idea.
好主意。

152
00:06:20,220 --> 00:06:23,220
I'd love that.
我很乐意。

153
00:06:23,220 --> 00:06:32,560
All right, let's take a look at three more key phrases on Fluency Builder Part 2.
好的，让我们看看流利度提升第二部分中的三个关键短语。

154
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:36,740
Fluency Builder So one phrase that we heard from this when
流利度提升 所以从这段对话中我们听到的一个短语是，当

155
00:06:36,740 --> 00:06:41,980
things started to get a little bit more personal, Michelle said, I often like to get together
话题开始变得更私人时，米歇尔说，我经常喜欢

156
00:06:41,980 --> 00:06:42,980
with friends.
和朋友聚在一起。

157
00:06:42,980 --> 00:06:45,760
So this phrase here is to get together with friends.
所以这个短语是“和朋友聚在一起”。

158
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:52,300
So to get together means to be united or go with friends somewhere.
所以“聚在一起”意思是联合或和朋友一起去某个地方。

159
00:06:52,300 --> 00:06:53,300
That's right.
没错。

160
00:06:53,300 --> 00:06:55,540
So we could also use the phrase to hang out.
所以我们也可以使用短语“一起出去玩”。

161
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:58,780
This means you're not doing anything in particular.
这意味着你没有在做什么特别的事情。

162
00:06:58,780 --> 00:07:04,140
You're not cooking or swimming or going shopping, but it just means you're together with your
你没有在做饭、游泳或购物，只是意味着你和你的

163
00:07:04,140 --> 00:07:05,140
friends.
朋友们在一起。

164
00:07:05,140 --> 00:07:06,140
You could be doing anything.
你可以做任何事情。

165
00:07:06,140 --> 00:07:07,540
Right, exactly.
对，没错。

166
